{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17518372","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17518372"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:03:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:03:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12913"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12913","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12913"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.06,0.53,0.01,0.01,0.4]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5351"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107262"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"5351","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/5351"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question","status":"accepted","createdAt":"2023-05-17T11:45:33+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-27T08:31:23+09:30","updatedAction":"commented","acceptedAt":"2023-10-15T17:58:51+10:30","editorNotifiedAt":null,"feedbackAt":"2025-09-29 13:28:59"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12913"}},"updatedBy":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"12201"}},"author":{"data":null},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89721"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"11"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"88"},{"type":"tags","id":"736"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1087"},{"type":"tags","id":"1094"},{"type":"tags","id":"1114"},{"type":"tags","id":"2701"},{"type":"tags","id":"3549"},{"type":"tags","id":"4174"},{"type":"tags","id":"4875"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"9805"},{"type":"contributions","id":"10073"},{"type":"contributions","id":"15519"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18250"},{"type":"contributions","id":"38419"}]},"lastContribution":{"data":null},"lastRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89721"}},"lastActivity":{"data":null},"lastFeedback":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107262","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107262"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 68-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department with three days of fever, productive cough, and increasing breathlessness. Over the past six months, she has experienced progressive difficulty with speech and swallowing, particularly with liquids. She has noticed increased drooling and has lost 8 kg in weight. She has also developed generalised muscle weakness and fasciculations. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears unwell. Her pulse rate is 110/min, blood pressure 135/85 mmHg, respiratory rate 24/min, SpO2 92% on room air, and temperature 38.5\u00b0C. She has dysarthric speech with tongue wasting and fasciculations. There are coarse crackles in both lung bases. Her upper and lower limb reflexes are brisk with preserved power.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely cause of her acute presentation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Community-acquired pneumonia","Aspiration pneumonia","Pulmonary embolism","Acute bronchitis","Lung cancer"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient presents with features suggestive of bulbar-onset motor neurone disease (MND), including progressive dysarthria, dysphagia, tongue wasting, fasciculations, and generalised weakness. The current acute presentation is consistent with aspiration pneumonia, a common complication of bulbar dysfunction in MND.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAspiration pneumonia\u003C/strong\u003E is the most likely diagnosis given her underlying neurological condition affecting swallowing. The combination of dysphagia and respiratory symptoms strongly suggests aspiration as the mechanism of infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECommunity-acquired pneumonia\u003C/strong\u003E is less likely as the primary diagnosis given the clear predisposing factor of bulbar dysfunction. While the presenting features could be similar, the history strongly suggests an aspiration mechanism.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPulmonary embolism\u003C/strong\u003E typically presents with pleuritic chest pain, dyspnoea, and hypoxia, but would not explain the productive cough and fever in this context.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAcute bronchitis\u003C/strong\u003E typically causes a cough but usually without significant systemic symptoms or abnormal vital signs as seen in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELung cancer\u003C/strong\u003E could present with similar respiratory symptoms, but the rapid onset and presence of fever make an infectious cause more likely. The weight loss in this case is better explained by dysphagia and reduced oral intake due to MND.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe management of this patient should include appropriate antibiotics, careful attention to positioning during feeding, and consideration of alternative feeding methods such as percutaneous endoscopic gastrostomy (PEG) to prevent future episodes of aspiration.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Aspiration pneumonia is a common complication of bulbar-onset motor neurone disease due to impaired swallowing","Progressive muscle weakness, particularly affecting speech and swallowing, is characteristic of bulbar-onset motor neurone disease","Early recognition of swallowing difficulties in motor neurone disease is crucial for preventing aspiration pneumonia"],"references":["Niedermeyer S, Murn M, Choi PJ. Respiratory Failure in Amyotrophic Lateral\u00a0Sclerosis. Chest. 2019 Feb;155(2):401-408. doi: 10.1016/j.chest.2018.06.035. Epub 2018 Jul 7. PMID: 29990478.","McDermott CJ, Shaw PJ. Diagnosis and management of motor neurone disease. BMJ. 2008 Mar 22;336(7645):658-62. doi: 10.1136/bmj.39493.511759.BE. PMID: 18356234; PMCID: PMC2270983.","Arora RD, Khan YS. Motor Neuron Disease. [Updated 2023 Aug 7]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK560774/","Wood-Allum C, Shaw PJ. Motor neurone disease: a practical update on diagnosis and management. Clin Med (Lond). 2010 Jun;10(3):252-8. doi: 10.7861/clinmedicine.10-3-252. PMID: 20726457; PMCID: PMC5873552."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89721"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12913"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89721","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89721"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-27T08:30:19+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-27T08:32:04+09:30","number":19,"notes":"","plagiarismCheckedAt":"2025-06-27T08:31:23+09:30","plagiarismScore":16.3,"plagiarismReportUrl":"https://emedici-copyleaks.syd1.digitaloceanspaces.com/plagiarism-report-5351-19.pdf?X-Amz-Content-Sha256=UNSIGNED-PAYLOAD\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=DO00QAKVE68N83EBLT2J%2F20250929%2Fsyd1%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20250929T043400Z\u0026X-Amz-SignedHeaders=host\u0026X-Amz-Expires=601200\u0026X-Amz-Signature=85280cbc0e8b628eec17b436109c919b64a4e81aff3a8a44138a261f1fc02aed"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"5351"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107262"}},"author":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"12201"}},"generation":{"data":null}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\